Aura's Inventory Tweaks (AIT) is a project whose goal is to improve Skyrim's inventory and related menus, with a specific focus on quality of life. Currently AIT uses SkyUI's config file and some KID files to make some sorting and informational tweaks which should hopefully make using item and magic menus more enjoyable.


[b][color=#ffd966]Aura's Inventory Tweaks
[/color][/b]

[b][color=#ffd966]The Problems[/color][/b]

SkyUI is a wonderful mod that improves Skyrim's inventory menu and other interfaces. That was the first mod I ever downloaded, and I would recommend to everyone. However, there are elements of it that I wasn't satisfied with.
[list=1]
[*]The first of these things was the look, for which I personally started using [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/23010]Dear Diary[/url]﻿, but there are plenty of great choices like [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/49881]Nordic UI[/url]﻿ and [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/60837]Dear Diary Dark Mode[/url]﻿.
[*]The second thing is sorting. You could consider me a hoarder. My goblin brain sees items, picks up items, repeat. Sorting through all that [s]junk[/s] shiny loot can be difficult with SkyUI's limited sorting function. It mostly just sorts items alphabetically by name, with no regard to if it is a sword, potion, or heavy shield. Some mods try and help with this aspect. [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/49095]Better SkyUI Config[/url]﻿ attempts to sort items by type, and [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/17601]SkyUI AIO Survival[/url]﻿ adds columns with more information to help you pick out what you want.
[*]The third thing I wasn't satisfied with was the classifications. SkyUI added 2 ways to help see at a glance what kind of item something is: an icon, and a type. For example, you can easily identify "Aversion to Frost" as a poison because of it's purple skull bottle icon and poison type. However, this feature is severely limited. The Ancient Nordic Pickaxe from the Dragonborn DLC doesn't have a pickaxe icon and typing. Notes don't have a note icon or type without the help of [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/32561]Fix Note Icon[/url]. Modded items like spears don't really fit in the vanilla types of greatsword or battleaxe, which inspired [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/37231]SkyUI Weapons Pack[/url]﻿.
[/list]
[b][color=#ffd966]The Solutions
[/color][/b]
There is always room for improvement. That's why I made Aura's Inventory Tweaks, to fill in some holes I saw. Here's how AIT tackles these issues:
[list=1]
[*]﻿AIT doesn't really touch aesthetics much, aside from icon colors. However, AIT offers several versions to work with your choice of SkyUI skin.
[*]AIT [b][i]COMPLETELY[/i][/b] overhauls sorting. I do this using a combination of [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/55728]Keyword Item Distributer[/url]﻿ inis and SkyUI's own config.txt to overhaul sorting. AIT does this by breaking apart items into hopefully intuitive groupings of categories and subcategories (open to feedback). I've also tried to put the best, strongest, and/or most used items or spells near the top.
[*]AIT tweaks and adds a ton of new classifications for all item types, allowing you to easily distinguish items like Black Soul Gems, Skill Books, [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/74054]Hand-Crossbows[/url]﻿, Cheese, Maps, Nodachi (2-handed katanas), and SO much more. This usually requires manually adding the items to the correct categories in a KID ini, so if you use a mod that isn't supported yet, let me know in the comments and I'll try to add it.
[/list]

