Q2:[/color][/b] X mod also includes the file "config.txt". Is AIT compatible with that mod?
[b][color=#93c47d]A2:[/color][/b] Check the compatibility section. As a general rule, if it modifies the file "/data/interface/skyui/config.txt", I've probably looked at it at some point while making AIT. I've probably either included support for it if applicable or it makes similar tweaks to AIT (in which case it's probably redundant). Just overwrite X mod with AIT and let me know if you think something's not working as intended.

[b][color=#93c47d]
Q3:[/color][/b] The icons and types aren't showing up in the crafting or favorites menus. Why?
[b][color=#93c47d]A3:[/color][/b] SkyUI wasn't actually coded to use the overwrite data from config.txt in those menus for some reason. I plan to try and fix this in a future update, but I will have to learn some ActionScript, and get permission from a couple authors to include their files in AIT.

[b][color=#93c47d]
Q4:[/color][/b] I want to put equipped items and/or unread books on top like [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/49095]BSC[/url]. How do I do that?
[b][color=#93c47d]A4:[/color][/b] In your inventory, select the default sorting arrow (at the top of the icon column) until it is pointing down. It will then sort the same as before, but put equipped weapons/armor/spells and unread books at the top.

[b][color=#93c47d]
Q5:[/color][/b] How do I change what info columns are visible?
[b][color=#93c47d]A5:[/color][/b] In your inventory, select the gear icon in the top-right corner and check or uncheck whatever columns you want until you're satisfied. Then save your game. SkyUI will remember your preferences for the rest of the save file.

If you want to change the default settings, check the spoiler.
[spoiler]
Go into the config, under [color=#8e7cc3][ListLayout][/color], and change [color=#8e7cc3].hidden[/color] to [color=#8e7cc3]true[/color] or [color=#8e7cc3]false[/color] on the columns you want.

For example you could change:
[color=#8e7cc3]﻿columns.valueWeightColumn.hidden = true[/color]
to
[color=#8e7cc3]﻿columns.valueWeightColumn.hidden = false[/color]
﻿[/spoiler]
[b][color=#93c47d]
Q6:[/color][/b] I want to change the text and/or icon colors. How would I do that?
[b][color=#93c47d]A6:[/color][/b] Go into the config and change the hex color code for the color you want to change. I like [url=https://convertingcolors.com/]this tool[/url] for messing with hex colors.
[b]
Entry Text Colors[/b]
